Reasoning: The paper focuses on communication techniques for a large-scale array of antennas, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed channel estimation and precoding techniques involve signal processing and optimization, which could also be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY). The use of Fourier/Laplace series and geometric modeling suggests a mathematical approach, which could be classified under multimedia (cs.MM) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
